<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-08-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                    <head>No. 503.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-08-14"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 14,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 57.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 14 of the 12th ultimo, in which you
                        communicate the text of your note of the 2d to the minister of state on the
                        general subject of the claims of our citizens growing out of the embargo of
                        their estates in Cuba during the late insurrection there, is approved. Your
                        Nos. 15–23 in separate cases of these claims have been read, and the action
                        which they report is commended.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>